# Platform OS Boundaries (ADR-023)

Layout: `Platform/` (kernel + services), `Modules/` (products), `Connectors/`, `AI/`, `apps/` (clients), `Packages/` (shared).

## Forbidden

- `Platform/*` importing `Modules/*` or `Connectors/*` domain code
- `Connectors/*` importing `Modules/*`
- Business logic in `apps/*` (API clients only)
- Cross-module Eloquent relations or direct table access
- Payment/shipping SDK calls outside FSL / Platform/Shipping contracts

## Allowed cross-package

- Domain events (async)
- Published query interfaces
- `Packages/shared/` value objects
- Platform service facades documented in module ARCHITECTURE.md

## New package scaffold

Follow [Module Template](V2.0/docs/00-meta/module-template.md): `module.json`, full `docs/` contract, ServiceProvider.

Cross-package communication: **events** or interfaces — never sync coupling that blocks scale.

Performance: no N+1; paginate all lists; queue side effects; tenant-prefixed cache keys.

See [Engineering Standards §13–16](V2.0/docs/00-meta/engineering-standards.md).
